Part XVI.  第十六部分
Legal and Policy  法律与政策
41. On being a Lawyer in FOSS  成为开源软件的律师
Till Jaeger

Dr. Till Jaeger has been a partner at JBB Rechtsanwaelte since 2001.
He is a Certified Copyright and Media Law Attorney and advises
large and medium-sized IT businesses as well as government authorities
and software developers on matters involving contracts, licensing
and online use. One particular focus of his work is on the legal issues
created by Free and Open Source Software. He is co-founder of the
Institute for Legal Aspects of Free & Open Source Software (ifrOSS).
He provides advice on compliance with open source licenses and on
compatibility issues, and helps developers and software companies to
enforce licenses. Till represented the gpl-violations.org project in several
lawsuits to enforce the GPL and has published several articles
and books related to legal questions of Free and Open Source Software.
He was a member of the Committee C in the GPLv3 drafting process.

Till Jaeger博士从2001年开始就成为JBB Rechtsanwaelte网站的一员。
他是一名专注于注册版权和媒体法的律师，为大型和中型IT企业以及政府当局和涉及合同纠纷的软件开发者、在线许可使用者提供建议。
他的一个重要核心工作是由自由开源软件引发的法律问题。
他是以解决自由开源软件法律问题的机构联合创始人(ifrOSS)。
他就符合开源许可证和兼容性问题提供建议，帮助开发者和软件公司强制执行许可。
Till 代表“GNU通用许可证—违规”项目在几个诉讼中强制执行通用许可证（GPL），并发表数篇文章，出版关于自由和开源软件法律问题的书籍。
他是起草第三版通用许可证（GPLv3）过程的C委员会成员之一。

One thing upfront: I am not a geek. I never have been one, and have
no intention of becoming one in the future.

事情的前提：我不是一个怪胎。我从来也不是一个反常的人，将来也没有意向成为其中的一员。

Instead, I am a lawyer. Most people who read this book probably
tend to sympathize more with geeks than with lawyers. Nevertheless,
I do not want to hide this fact. That the FOSS community is not
necessarily fond of lawyers but busy developing software is something
I did know about FOSS in early 1999 when our ways rst crossed.
But there were also quite a few things I did not know.

相反，我是一名律师。
相比于律师，大部分阅读这本书的人更倾向于同情怪胎。
然而，我不想隐瞒这个事实。
该开源软件社区不一定喜欢律师，却忙于开发软件，这是我所知道关于1999年初期开源软件的事情 ，那时我们提出了方法——rst交叉。
但是这里也有一些我所不知道的事情。
























